<td class=3D"column column-1" width=3D"100%" style=3D"mso-table-lspace: 0pt=
; mso-table-rspace: 0pt; font-weight: 400; text-align: left; padding-left: =
24px; padding-right: 24px; padding-top: 16px; vertical-align: top; border-t=
op: 0px; border-right: 0px; border-bottom: 0px; border-left: 0px;">
<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace: 0pt; mso-table-rspace: 0pt; wo=
rd-break: break-word;">
<tbody><tr>
<td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;">
<div style=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;=
Arial&#39;;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:15=
0%;text-align:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;">
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">Not 48 hours after <strong>Trum=
p</strong>=E2=80=99s Office of Management and Budget incited abject <em>cha=
os</em> in Washington by ordering the freeze of some $3 trillion in federal=
 spending, the White House appeared to back down=E2=80=94rescinding the off=
ending memo while claiming that the =E2=80=9Cfederal funding freeze=E2=80=
=9D still stood. <em>Whoops! </em>The administration, naturally, blamed the=
 media for the turmoil, with top advisor <strong>Stephen Miller</strong> <a=
 href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2Uktxcl=
JLZ0dVdFRTV0dUcEFiQ2FuVnFLenZmRT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly94LmNvbS9TdGVwaGVuT=
S9zdGF0dXMvMTg4NDM2NjA5MzUzMzI0MTczND91dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249VGhlK0Jlc3QrJTI2K1Ro=
ZStCcmlnaHRlc3QrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxJTJGMjklMkYyNSUyOVx1MDAyNnV0bV9jb25=
0ZW50PVRoZStCZXN0KyUyNitUaGUrQnJpZ2h0ZXN0Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjI5JT=
JGMjUlMjlcdTAwMjZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsX2FjdGlvblx1MDAyNnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9Y3Vzd=
G9tZXIuaW9cdTAwMjZ1dG1fdGVybT1mNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJpbnRlcm5hbCI6ImY2=
YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImxpbmtfaWQiOjIwNjQ3Mzl9/5839b833e7076cfdca1a4e089c=
81f90ad4e4e146a9f894d5ed753b16acf6f7ec" style=3D"text-decoration: underline=
; color: #d40000;">calling</a> the outcry =E2=80=9Cthe first dumb media hoa=
x of 2025=E2=80=9D just a day before the O.M.B. reversed course.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">Whatever happens to this specif=
ic memo=E2=80=94a judge <a href=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9p=
ZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0dVdFRTV0dUcEFiQ2FuVnFLenZmRT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR=
0cHM6Ly93d3cubnl0aW1lcy5jb20vMjAyNS8wMS8yOS91cy9wb2xpdGljcy90cnVtcC1hbnRpLX=
dva2UtZnVuZGluZy5odG1sP3V0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzd=
CstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJTKyUyODElMkYyOSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX2NvbnRlbnQ9VGhlK0Jl=
c3QrJTI2K1RoZStCcmlnaHRlc3QrLStTVUJTQ1JJQkVSUyslMjgxJTJGMjklMkYyNSUyOVx1MDA=
yNnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWxfYWN0aW9uXHUwMDI2dXRtX3NvdXJjZT1jdXN0b21lci5pb1x1MD=
AyNnV0bV90ZXJtPWY2YzYwNjE3ZGE0MmFiZDEyYSIsImludGVybmFsIjoiZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyY=
WJkMTJhIiwibGlua19pZCI6MjA2NDc3OX0/7b3bb79274c5bdf4fb08700994faa3042daf9c3e=
a00ef2ce0bc8bc413dc93852" style=3D"text-decoration: underline; color: #d400=
00;">is now set</a> to issue a restraining order=E2=80=94there=E2=80=99s no=
 question that the constitutional showdown is (or was) consistent with the =
president=E2=80=99s broader intention to arrogate more power to the executi=
ve branch and sideline Congress. Democrats are taking a cautious mini-victo=
ry lap for now, but <em>no one</em> on Capitol Hill thinks Trump is going t=
o start operating within the confines of the law, or precedent, as it perta=
ins to Congress=E2=80=99s power of the purse.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">During his first nine days, Tru=
mp has outdone even himself, testing the bounds of the presidency more quic=
kly and aggressively than at any point during his first term. Just as notab=
ly, he=E2=80=99s pushed the envelope with the tacit (and often explicit) ap=
proval of congressional Republicans, who have said almost nothing about his=
 decision to ignore a bipartisan law banning TikTok; to fire some 17 inspec=
tors general without giving Congress 30 days=E2=80=99 notice; to purge the =
Justice Department of lawyers who worked on January 6 cases; and to fire me=
mbers of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission and the National Labor=
 Relations Board=E2=80=94the latest in a series of actions the president ca=
nnot <em>legally</em> execute.=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0px;">Once again, we=E2=80=99re in sh=
ocking but not surprising territory. Trump was elected, after all, on the p=
romise that he would radically reshape the federal government and defang th=
e =E2=80=9CDeep State.=E2=80=9D Indeed, the blueprint for the executive act=
ions he=E2=80=99s taken in the past week had been clearly spelled out in Pr=
oject 2025, the Heritage Foundation=E2=80=99s 900-page governance agenda th=
at Trump repeatedly disavowed on the campaign trail. Now, of course, one of=
 the project=E2=80=99s chief architects, <strong>Russell Vought</strong>, h=
as been tapped to lead O.M.B.=C2=A0=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 0;"><br/>Vought semi-foreshadowed these past nine days =
in Project 2025=E2=80=99s manifesto on presidential power. =E2=80=9CThe gre=
at challenge confronting a conservative president,=E2=80=9D Vought <a href=
=3D"https://email.puck.news/e/c/eyJlbWFpbF9pZCI6ImRnVDJ4Z1lEQUt2UktxclJLZ0d=
VdFRTV0dUcEFiQ2FuVnFLenZmRT0iLCJocmVmIjoiaHR0cHM6Ly9zdGF0aWMucHJvamVjdDIwMj=
Uub3JnLzIwMjVfTWFuZGF0ZUZvckxlYWRlcnNoaXBfRlVMTC5wZGY_dXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPVRoZ=
StCZXN0KyUyNitUaGUrQnJpZ2h0ZXN0Ky0rU1VCU0NSSUJFUlMrJTI4MSUyRjI5JTJGMjUlMjlc=
dTAwMjZ1dG1fY29udGVudD1UaGUrQmVzdCslMjYrVGhlK0JyaWdodGVzdCstK1NVQlNDUklCRVJ=
TKyUyODElMkYyOSUyRjI1JTI5XHUwMDI2dXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbF9hY3Rpb25cdTAwMjZ1dG=
1fc291cmNlPWN1c3RvbWVyLmlvXHUwMDI2dXRtX3Rlcm09ZjZjNjA2MTdkYTQyYWJkMTJhIiwia=
W50ZXJuYWwiOiJmNmM2MDYxN2RhNDJhYmQxMmEiLCJsaW5rX2lkIjoyMDY0NzgwfQ/5116b7eb6=
032a9332c2d8ace797dcc60b3d1b2f6ed4540d26310ad8e3e0a9042" style=3D"text-deco=
ration: underline; color: #d40000;">wrote</a>, =E2=80=9Cis the existential =
need for aggressive use of the vast powers of the executive branch to retur=
n power=E2=80=94including power currently held by the executive branch=E2=
=80=94to the American people.=E2=80=9D So far, he=E2=80=99s only hitting th=
e =E2=80=9Caggressive use=E2=80=9D part. Republican Senator <strong>Kevin C=
ramer</strong>, always good for a dose of honesty, acknowledged that Trump =
is =E2=80=9Ctesting his power,=E2=80=9D adding that the Founders probably w=
ouldn=E2=80=99t agree with such an expansive view of the presidency.</p>
</div>
